      • isSingleton

        public static boolean isSingleton(JDDNode dd,
                                  JDDVars vars)
        Returns if dd is a single satisfying assignment to the variables in vars.
        This is the case if there is a single path to the ONE constant and exactly the variables of vars occur on the path.
        Note: The variables in vars have to sorted in increasing index order! Use JDDVars.sortByIndex() to achieve this if the ordering is not guaranteed by construction.
        Parameters:
        dd - the DD
        vars - the variables

      • PrintMinterms

        public static void PrintMinterms(PrismLog log,
                                 JDDNode dd,
                                 JDDVars vars,
                                 java.lang.String description)
        Print the minterms for a JDDNode over the variables vars.
        Positive variables are marked with 1, negatives with 0 and don't cares are marked with -
        vars has to be ordered with increasing variable indizes and has to contain all variables in the support of dd.
        [ REFS: none, DEREFS: dd ]
        Parameters:
        log - the output log
        dd - the MTBDD
        vars - JDDVars of the relevant variables
        description - an optional description to be printed (null for none)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if vars does not fullfil the constraints

      • PrintMintermsRec

        private static void PrintMintermsRec(PrismLog log,
                                     JDDNode dd,
                                     JDDVars vars,
                                     int cur_index,
                                     char[] minterm)
        Recursively print the minterms for a JDDNode over the variables vars.
        Positive variables are marked with 1, negatives with 0 and don't cares are marked with -
        vars has to be ordered with increasing variable indizes and has to contain all variables in the support of dd.
        [ REFS: none, DEREFS: none ]

        log - the output log
        dd - the MTBDD
        vars - JDDVars of the relevant variables
        cur_index - the current index into vars
        minterm - character array of length vars.n() storing the current (partial) minterm
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if vars does not fullfil the constraints

      • Export3dMatrixToPPFile

        public static void Export3dMatrixToPPFile(JDDNode dd,
                                          JDDVars rvars,
                                          JDDVars cvars,
                                          JDDVars nvars,
                                          java.lang.String filename)
        Given a BDD that represents transition matrices of an MDP, this method outputs one matrix for every action. Note that the output is in fact not a PP file, but several PP files concatenated into one file. For example, for a model with the variable x : [0..2]; and transitions [a] (x=0) -> 0.3:(x'=1) + 0.7:(x'=2); [b] (x=0) -> 1:(x'=2); [a] (x=2) -> (x'=1); [a] (x=1) -> (x'=0); the output would be (e.g.) 4 4 0 2 1.000000 4 0 1 0.300000 1 0 1.000000 0 2 0.700000 2 1 1.000000 4 [ REFS: none, DEREFS: none ]
